The reading for 丁 is an unexpected one. It's てい instead of ちょう, so think about how the street is lined with <reading>ta</reading>ter (てい) tots, and how you can eat from them as you walk along on your trek. How <vocabulary>polite</vocabulary> of someone to leave them there for you!

Imagine that a <vocabulary>cool breeze</vocabulary> is pushing your little <reading>row</reading> (りょう) boat along, so that you don't need to do any rowing. Ahh, what a nice cool breeze…
